    "description": "This prints out a better error message when someone tries to install yt with a too-old version of setuptools installed. To test this I created a virtualenv with setuptools 17.1.1 installed. With this pull request, we now print out a better error message when either directly invoking setup.py or when installing via pip:\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n#!bash\r\n\r\n$ ~/Documents/test/old-setuptools/bin/python setup.py develop\r\nyt currently requires setuptools 18.0 or newer\r\nCurrently setuptools 17.1.1 is installed\r\nPlease update setuptools in your python environment then try again\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n#!bash\r\n\r\n$ ~/Documents/test/old-setuptools/bin/pip install -e .\r\nObtaining file:///Users/goldbaum/Documents/yt-hg\r\n    Complete output from command python setup.py egg_info:\r\n    yt currently requires setuptools 18.0 or newer\r\n    Currently setuptools 17.1.1 is installed\r\n    Please update setuptools in your python environment then try again\r\n\r\n\r\n    ----------------------------------------\r\nCommand \"python setup.py egg_info\" failed with error code 1 in /Users/goldbaum/Documents/yt-hg\r\n```\r\n\r\nI'm happy to adjust the wording of this error message if people feel it's too vague. I wanted to err against suggesting to run `pip install -U setuptools` since that will only work well for a subset of python installations (e.g. not conda, python is installed in a location that doesn't require root privileges).",
